IDENTIFICATION DIVISION.
PROGRAM-ID. SIMPLE-FILE-MOVER.
AUTHOR. SIMON MIKKELSEN.
* This program doth move files from one place to another
* With great haste and precision, like a swift courier
* It doth read from the source and write to the destination
* With nary a care for the contents, only the path matters

ENVIRONMENT DIVISION.
INPUT-OUTPUT SECTION.
FILE-CONTROL.
    SELECT SOURCE-FILE ASSIGN TO 'source.txt'
     ORGANIZATION IS LINE SEQUENTIAL.
    SELECT DESTINATION-FILE ASSIGN TO 'destination.txt'
     ORGANIZATION IS LINE SEQUENTIAL.

DATA DIVISION.
FILE SECTION.
FD  SOURCE-FILE.
01  SOURCE-RECORD PIC X(100).

FD  DESTINATION-FILE.
01  DESTINATION-RECORD PIC X(100).

WORKING-STORAGE SECTION.
01  EOF-FLAG PIC X VALUE 'N'.
01  TEMP-RECORD PIC X(100).
01  UNUSED-VARIABLE PIC X(100).
01  GOLLUM PIC X(100).
01  FRODO PIC X(100).

PROCEDURE DIVISION.
OPEN-FILES.
    OPEN INPUT SOURCE-FILE.
    OPEN OUTPUT DESTINATION-FILE.
    PERFORM UNTIL EOF-FLAG = 'Y'
     READ SOURCE-FILE INTO TEMP-RECORD
         AT END
          MOVE 'Y' TO EOF-FLAG
         NOT AT END
          MOVE TEMP-RECORD TO DESTINATION-RECORD
          WRITE DESTINATION-RECORD
     END-READ
    END-PERFORM.
    CLOSE SOURCE-FILE.
    CLOSE DESTINATION-FILE.
    STOP RUN.
